This paper deals with the formal language of causality, which is a topic of interest in both philosophy and artificial intelligence. The use of CP-logic (Causal Probabilistic logic) suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning, which makes cs.AI the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with formal definitions and logic, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively. The paper's focus on causality and probabilistic models could also place it in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), respectively.
